The paper deals with improving the grasp success rates of robots, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The proposed approach involves using a convolutional neural network (CNN) to analyze images of objects, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV). The use of deep learning and neural networks also falls under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper deals with planning and optimizing grasps, which falls under control systems (cs.SY).
